WEBVTT

00:01.920 --> 00:03.194
NARRATOR: Erstwhile
on Fargo...

00:03.280 --> 00:05.920
I'm not afraid of a war.
But are you with me?

00:06.000 --> 00:08.037
We're not gonna
make the first move.

00:09.200 --> 00:13.592
But if these Kansas City mooks
come at ya shootin',

00:16.040 --> 00:18.600
we'll cut the goddamn
nose off their face.

00:18.840 --> 00:20.194
MIKE: Your Indian killed him.

00:20.320 --> 00:21.515
I didn't know
that was happening.

00:21.600 --> 00:24.240
I wanna know what they're
gonna do before they do it.

00:24.520 --> 00:26.716
Otherwise, you can die
with the rest of 'em.

00:31.320 --> 00:33.152
BEAR: You sent my goddamn son?

00:34.120 --> 00:35.394
The kid said it
should be family

00:35.520 --> 00:36.794
that pulls the trigger,
which is true.

00:37.120 --> 00:38.315
He's 17.

00:38.400 --> 00:40.198
Sheriff?
Go inside now, Peggy.

00:40.800 --> 00:43.918
When I find you, darling,
I'm gonna make you bleed.

00:56.440 --> 00:58.829
And that,
there's a word for that.

01:00.080 --> 01:02.356
It's called "managing up".

01:02.480 --> 01:07.680
Which, if you want to rise to any
kind of power in this organization,

01:07.760 --> 01:09.239
is something
you'd better learn.

01:10.760 --> 01:14.719
Because they'll say to you,
"Go out, do the job,

01:14.800 --> 01:16.677
"and don't worry."

01:16.760 --> 01:19.149
But in fact,
what they mean...

01:21.760 --> 01:24.320
Is talk them
through it.

01:24.400 --> 01:25.720
You understand?

01:26.600 --> 01:29.114
It doesn't matter if
it's washing machines

01:29.200 --> 01:33.159
or cocaine,
whores or horseradish,

01:33.720 --> 01:38.078
they, the powers that be,
they need to know...

01:45.880 --> 01:47.951
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

02:17.040 --> 02:19.077
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

02:19.280 --> 02:21.317
(GASPING)

02:21.560 --> 02:23.551
(JETHRO TULL'S
LOCOMOTIVE BREATH PLAYING)

02:30.400 --> 02:32.755
(SINGING)
In the shuffling madness

02:33.720 --> 02:36.075
Of the locomotive breath

02:38.080 --> 02:40.913
Runs the all-time loser

02:41.720 --> 02:43.950
Headlong to his death

02:44.760 --> 02:47.878
Oh, he feels
the piston scraping

02:48.760 --> 02:51.991
Steam breaking on his brow

02:53.000 --> 02:55.799
Oh, thank God,
he stole the handle

02:56.200 --> 02:59.272
And the train
it won't stop going

02:59.360 --> 03:01.715
No way to slow down

03:03.640 --> 03:05.597
Oh, oh

03:08.920 --> 03:11.309
He sees his
children jumping off

03:12.600 --> 03:14.637
At the stations, one by one

03:16.440 --> 03:18.670
His woman and
his best friend

03:18.800 --> 03:19.790
(GUNSHOT)

03:19.960 --> 03:22.554
In bed and having fun

03:23.080 --> 03:26.391
Oh, oh, he's
crawling down the corridor

03:27.600 --> 03:30.274
On his hands and knees

03:31.120 --> 03:34.112
Old Charlie stole the handle

03:34.640 --> 03:37.712
And the train
it won't stop going

03:37.800 --> 03:40.155
No way to slow down

03:41.480 --> 03:43.994
Hey, hey

04:02.400 --> 04:04.437
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

04:05.720 --> 04:07.757
(HORSE NEIGHING)

04:10.920 --> 04:12.957
(DOG BARKING IN THE DISTANCE)

04:27.480 --> 04:28.834
We waited.

04:29.760 --> 04:30.955
I don't like funerals.

04:31.080 --> 04:32.832
Nobody likes funerals.

04:34.840 --> 04:37.639
We wanna thank you boys from
coming out from Buffalo, helping us out.

04:38.360 --> 04:40.476
We couldn't have fought
them off much longer.

04:40.560 --> 04:42.278
Forget about it.

04:42.360 --> 04:46.957
I'm seeing cows, horses,
what do you have... Chickens?

04:47.040 --> 04:49.714
It's like wild goddamn
kingdom in here. (LAUGHS)

04:53.800 --> 04:54.915
We got ups and downs.

04:55.040 --> 04:56.155
Tell me.

04:56.240 --> 04:57.833
Go see to lunch.

04:57.920 --> 05:01.038
I'm grown.
I can hear.

05:09.680 --> 05:12.832
We got five of theirs.
Including management.

05:13.640 --> 05:16.075
But they felled
Roost and Seymour.

05:17.560 --> 05:19.949
That means South
Dakota's turned.

05:20.680 --> 05:22.079
Which Bear now tells
me is where they got

05:22.160 --> 05:24.390
the presidents' faces up
on the side of a rock?

05:26.360 --> 05:28.078
So we should get that back.

05:30.480 --> 05:32.869
Nothing from Hanzee?
Nothing.

05:33.600 --> 05:34.635
Two days.

05:35.280 --> 05:37.430
What about my dad?

05:41.560 --> 05:43.312
Gonna need a third
hole is my feeling.

05:43.680 --> 05:45.398
Have some respect.

05:45.920 --> 05:48.912
My lion didn't raise that boy to
be killed by small-town muscle.

05:50.200 --> 05:51.554
Thought that about Rye.

05:53.320 --> 05:54.674
Now there's nothing
left but clothes.

05:54.760 --> 05:56.512
They're just men.

05:58.520 --> 05:59.555
What are you saying?

06:00.280 --> 06:01.475
I said,

06:01.560 --> 06:03.710
it's not like my dad's
the shark in that movie,

06:03.840 --> 06:05.638
we're gonna
need a bigger boat.

06:06.520 --> 06:07.999
He shits and sleeps.

06:09.400 --> 06:11.198
I swear, I thought your
father was the problem.

06:11.280 --> 06:15.433
His nature, and towards women,
but you're two of the same.

06:16.120 --> 06:18.873
You're porcupines! You're half
crazy, always looking for a fight.

06:21.760 --> 06:23.114
This family

06:24.480 --> 06:26.278
deserves the ground.

06:31.480 --> 06:32.550
I got this.

06:35.440 --> 06:38.398
Hey, porcupine.
Hey. Where you running?

06:38.480 --> 06:40.312
I shouldn't have hit her.

06:41.320 --> 06:42.958
Hitting is the least of it.
(ENGINE STARTING)

06:43.480 --> 06:45.676
Not enough of us left
to start telling the truth.

06:45.800 --> 06:47.234
SIMONE: Go to hell.

06:54.360 --> 06:56.397
(SIRENS WAILING)

07:00.600 --> 07:02.910
Last stand?
Make a run for it?

07:03.000 --> 07:03.990
(CAR DOORS OPEN AND CLOSE)

07:05.320 --> 07:06.310
FLOYD: Benjamin.

07:06.440 --> 07:07.430
Floyd.

07:07.520 --> 07:08.635
It's funeral day.

07:08.760 --> 07:09.830
I know.

07:11.240 --> 07:13.675
We waited till
the dirt settled.

07:14.840 --> 07:15.875
But, now I need
you to come with us.

07:18.360 --> 07:19.953
It's me you should
be taking.

07:20.080 --> 07:21.673
No. You're good.

07:24.480 --> 07:25.470
Floyd.

07:30.640 --> 07:32.677
(CAR DOOR OPENS)

07:49.200 --> 07:52.192
How's my boy? State
pen, awaiting trial.

07:52.920 --> 07:55.958
You should visit.
Where's your brother?

07:56.560 --> 07:57.880
Found Jesus.

07:58.600 --> 07:59.590
Mmm.

07:59.800 --> 08:01.473
Joined a monastery.

08:02.800 --> 08:04.199
I just bet.

08:04.720 --> 08:06.711
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

08:23.480 --> 08:24.595
Phone.

08:25.040 --> 08:26.599
Take a message.

08:30.360 --> 08:32.078
You're gonna wanna
take this one, bro.

08:32.280 --> 08:33.953
The prick says he
knows where Dodd is.

08:39.760 --> 08:41.239
Take the message.

09:00.800 --> 09:01.870
CHIEF: Tell me one more time.

09:01.960 --> 09:04.520
Why is Floyd Gerhardt
sitting in my interview room?

09:04.720 --> 09:07.917
BEN: Sir,
Trooper Solverson and myself,

09:08.000 --> 09:09.673
we're tired of
playing cleanup.

09:10.440 --> 09:11.635
Officially.

09:11.920 --> 09:14.434
Thought we'd apply some
pressure to both sides.

09:14.520 --> 09:17.672
Let them know all this killing
isn't going unnoticed.

09:18.240 --> 09:19.469
What about
this butcher?

09:19.600 --> 09:23.753
We've got an APB out on both
Blumquists, Ed and Peggy. So far, nothing.

09:23.920 --> 09:25.718
Could be on the run.
Could be dead.

09:27.160 --> 09:28.719
I should have
checked on that girl.

09:30.680 --> 09:34.514
Eliot Ness himself deputized
my daddy, ATF, during Prohibition.

09:36.120 --> 09:38.396
He used to tell stories
of tommy-gun bloodbaths

09:38.480 --> 09:40.312
and heads
rolling in the road.

09:41.680 --> 09:44.354
Never thought I'd see it in
my lifetime. But here we are.

09:45.560 --> 09:47.153
This thing's just
plum out of control.

09:49.640 --> 09:50.835
What do you think?

09:51.520 --> 09:53.670
I think I wanna
live in a world where

09:53.800 --> 09:55.711
people leave
the front door unlocked.

09:55.800 --> 09:56.790
(GRUNTS)

09:57.000 --> 09:58.832
Probably, we're just
wasting our breath.

10:01.440 --> 10:02.555
Okay.

10:03.120 --> 10:06.954
You two go see the out-of-towners.
Leave the old broad to us.

10:18.880 --> 10:20.871
(CLEARS THROAT)
I'm gonna smoke.

10:28.800 --> 10:31.918
Ma'am, I'm Sheriff Larsson,
Rock County.

10:33.360 --> 10:36.034
Had some differences with
your oldest boy yesterday.

10:36.840 --> 10:38.035
How'd that go for you?

10:38.880 --> 10:40.951
(CHUCKLES)
Let's call it a draw.

10:41.040 --> 10:43.111
On account of your
Indian sucker-punched me

10:43.200 --> 10:44.429
before I could
make a showing.

10:45.600 --> 10:47.750
(CHUCKLING)
Yeah, he does that.

10:50.000 --> 10:51.513
HANK: Sorry
to hear about Otto.

10:54.880 --> 10:56.518
They shot him in his own home,

10:58.480 --> 11:00.596
these Kansas
City hosenscheiBer.

11:01.280 --> 11:04.716
Children sleeping upstairs.
Savages.

11:06.360 --> 11:10.558
My wife passed last summer. We
were up in Brainerd visiting my sister.

11:11.440 --> 11:15.434
The last thing she said to me,
"Do you smell toast?"

11:17.800 --> 11:20.838
Different roads.
Same destination.

11:20.920 --> 11:22.069
I suppose.

11:22.320 --> 11:24.038
But the question is,
for you I mean,

11:25.120 --> 11:26.440
how far does it go?

11:27.760 --> 11:30.274
Husband dead,
plus your youngest.

11:31.280 --> 11:34.955
Grandson in jail. And now,
Dodd's missing, we hear.

11:36.800 --> 11:39.030
Old timers had it worse.

11:39.120 --> 11:43.796
Used to be 10 born,
two survived.

11:44.640 --> 11:49.396
Consumption, scalpings,
smallpox, wolves.

11:49.960 --> 11:52.952
Well, it's a question of what
you can live with, I suppose.

11:53.040 --> 11:54.269
How many ghosts.

11:56.120 --> 11:59.636
I shot a man through the teeth
in Vichy France.

12:01.560 --> 12:03.949
I still see his face
every night before bed.

12:08.120 --> 12:09.519
Our back is to the wall.

12:11.080 --> 12:12.070
You see that, yeah?

12:12.160 --> 12:15.391
Yeah, except I'm the guy in the
next state who got shanghaied,

12:15.480 --> 12:17.551
and your sons are the ones
that took the drive.

12:17.640 --> 12:19.392
The Butcher of
Luverne killed my boy!

12:20.240 --> 12:22.197
On orders from Kansas City.

12:22.360 --> 12:24.954
I've known Ed Blumquist
since short pants.

12:25.040 --> 12:28.715
If he's working for the Kansas
City mob, I'll cut off my toe.

12:30.840 --> 12:34.231
What's it they call those
Russians? "Sleeper agents?”

12:36.320 --> 12:40.359
I'm saying, you think you know
someone, but what do you know, really?

12:40.600 --> 12:42.557
I even had a kid in
here the other day,

12:43.240 --> 12:45.675
stabbed his parents
to death in their sleep.

12:46.360 --> 12:48.033
When I asked him why,
he couldn't say.

12:49.320 --> 12:51.118
Just come over him
all of a sudden.

12:54.640 --> 12:56.870
Stories used to be
simpler, that's for sure.

12:59.040 --> 13:00.189
This, then that.

13:00.800 --> 13:04.350
And now, I don't know
where it starts or how it ends.

13:06.040 --> 13:07.360
I truly don't.

13:07.960 --> 13:09.439
Without being simplistic,

13:10.920 --> 13:12.877
this thing's over
when you say it's over.

13:14.360 --> 13:17.990
No. They won't stop.
My boys.

13:19.200 --> 13:21.396
They've lost too much.
They're too proud.

13:24.600 --> 13:29.231
Well, okay, then.
How about you help us out?

13:29.920 --> 13:31.831
You know these
Kansas City fellas.

13:31.920 --> 13:33.513
Point us in
the right direction there.

13:33.720 --> 13:36.234
You know,
weaknesses, indiscretions.

13:37.000 --> 13:39.389
Give us something actionable,
and maybe,

13:39.720 --> 13:43.236
we make this whole northern
expansion unpalatable.

13:47.080 --> 13:48.070
Snitch.

13:48.680 --> 13:49.909
HANK: Well,

13:50.760 --> 13:52.319
you said yourself,

13:52.800 --> 13:55.838
hard to be simple
in times of complication.

13:59.920 --> 14:00.876
(JUST DROPPED IN
PLAYING ON RADIO)

14:00.960 --> 14:03.793
(SINGING)
The sundown shinin'in

14:06.560 --> 14:08.437
I found my mind

14:08.520 --> 14:11.592
In a brown paper bag within

14:15.080 --> 14:18.072
I tripped on a cloud
and fell eight miles high

14:18.440 --> 14:22.229
I tore my mind
on a jagged sky

14:22.320 --> 14:25.358
I just dropped in
to see what...

14:25.440 --> 14:27.113
Son of a bitch.

14:29.840 --> 14:33.356
Argh! You son of a bitch.

14:39.640 --> 14:40.630
(MUSIC STOPS)

14:41.440 --> 14:43.477
(PANTING)

14:55.000 --> 14:59.756
MIKE: Yes, sir. Maybe "under
control" was the wrong phrase,

15:00.480 --> 15:01.754
given what's happened.

15:01.840 --> 15:04.673
MAN: (OVER PHONE) You said,
when they killed Bulo, you said

15:04.840 --> 15:07.639
this Gerhardt outfit
was a stuffed shirt.

15:08.160 --> 15:10.549
Now I'm standing here
with blood on my socks?

15:10.880 --> 15:11.915
MIKE: I can handle it.

15:12.000 --> 15:12.990
The hell, you say.

15:14.160 --> 15:16.071
Braverman stood for you.

15:16.160 --> 15:20.631
Said, "He's not like the other
darkies. This one's smart. Capable."

15:20.760 --> 15:23.559
Sir... But that is
not what I'm seeing.

15:25.640 --> 15:28.598
And I appreciate
the opportunity, sir,

15:29.720 --> 15:32.394
believing as I do,
like the good Dr. King said,

15:33.840 --> 15:36.593
"A man should be judged on
the content of his character,

15:36.680 --> 15:37.795
"not the color of his skin."

15:38.040 --> 15:41.396
Yeah, he's dead. You're
gonna need a different quote.

15:41.880 --> 15:44.918
MIKE: I can break this family.
Two weeks.

15:46.240 --> 15:49.835
You got two days, then
I'm sending The Undertaker.

15:52.520 --> 15:55.876
Yes, sir.
Thank you, sir.

16:07.440 --> 16:11.718
You son of a bitch!
You son of a bitch!

16:13.000 --> 16:15.640
"Freedom, that terrible word
inscribed upon the chariot in the storm."

16:16.440 --> 16:17.555
What?

16:19.080 --> 16:20.150
You want me
to repeat it?

16:21.280 --> 16:23.157
Is that a quote?
Maybe.

16:24.560 --> 16:25.994
What do you want,
little girl?

16:26.080 --> 16:29.835
You were supposed to kill
my dad, not the old cripple.

16:30.080 --> 16:31.354
What's the difference?

16:31.440 --> 16:32.430
SIMONE: What?

16:33.480 --> 16:35.278
To quote Louis XVI,

16:37.080 --> 16:39.799
"Est-ce une révolte?”

16:39.880 --> 16:43.157
"Non, Sire,
c'est une revolution.”

16:46.880 --> 16:48.518
The Duke of La Rochefoucauld.

16:48.600 --> 16:52.992
Are we gonna talk or are you just
gonna quote the thesaurus at me?

16:53.240 --> 16:55.595
I mean, if the goal is to
kill those who oppress you,

16:57.440 --> 16:58.555
what does it
matter who goes first?

16:58.640 --> 17:01.280
Because, I said...

17:01.360 --> 17:02.759
Now, ironically,

17:04.200 --> 17:06.839
in astronomy, the word
"revolution" means

17:06.960 --> 17:11.238
a celestial object
that comes full circle.

17:12.960 --> 17:13.950
Did you know that?

17:14.640 --> 17:17.075
Which, if you think about it,
is pretty funny,

17:18.800 --> 17:22.430
considering here on Earth,
it means change.

17:22.960 --> 17:24.108
SIMONE: You're nuts.

17:25.200 --> 17:27.714
I'm talking about a promise.

17:28.119 --> 17:31.829
You could have killed me,
shooting up the house. Or Grandma.

17:32.360 --> 17:33.395
Argh!

17:33.480 --> 17:34.470
Unless...

17:36.920 --> 17:38.911
Would you say you're
her favorite? Who?

17:39.000 --> 17:40.513
The materfamilias.

17:41.640 --> 17:43.233
In my experience,

17:44.560 --> 17:47.951
the first-born
granddaughter, well,

17:49.760 --> 17:51.717
she's always
the shine on the apple.

17:52.600 --> 17:54.591
Oh, God.

17:54.880 --> 17:56.871
(SOBBING)

17:58.560 --> 18:00.631
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

18:03.560 --> 18:04.550
(SIMONE GASPS)

18:06.760 --> 18:07.830
(SCREAMS) Help!

18:11.040 --> 18:12.030
(GRUNTING)

18:12.920 --> 18:13.910
(GRUNTING)

18:22.160 --> 18:23.195
Wow.

18:23.520 --> 18:25.318
You okay there, miss?

18:27.200 --> 18:28.759
I am now.

18:29.800 --> 18:31.154
Walk her out, huh?

18:32.040 --> 18:33.189
What about you?

18:33.280 --> 18:34.679
I'm not saying
don't come back.

19:00.880 --> 19:02.871
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)
(DOORS SLIDE OPEN)

19:15.800 --> 19:17.074
I'm a big girl.

19:19.080 --> 19:21.276
You don't have
to nursemaid me.

19:22.640 --> 19:24.392
Floyd know you're here?

19:26.480 --> 19:27.675
Yeah.

19:28.680 --> 19:32.071
Yeah, I've seen you around.
Up at the compound.

19:32.800 --> 19:33.790
Seen me?

19:37.200 --> 19:38.759
Or watched me?

19:40.360 --> 19:44.035
I'm aware, I'm saying, that
the last place you should be

19:44.160 --> 19:45.958
is in a hotel room
with those fellas,

19:46.120 --> 19:47.918
especially given
what's happening.

19:49.920 --> 19:52.434
You won't tell though,

19:54.280 --> 19:55.315
will you?

19:59.120 --> 20:00.952
I don't have to.

20:05.320 --> 20:07.357
(GROANING)

20:07.560 --> 20:09.233
Oh, Jesus! Jesus!

20:10.240 --> 20:11.230
Oh.

20:11.400 --> 20:14.040
If I'm going to the
noose, I'm going.

20:14.440 --> 20:16.795
But I'm done
lying down for men.

20:16.960 --> 20:18.997
(BEN GROANING)

20:21.880 --> 20:22.870
Oh.

20:23.960 --> 20:24.950
(BLOWING)

20:38.160 --> 20:39.309
(ENGINE REVS)

20:42.480 --> 20:43.470
Hey.

20:45.000 --> 20:45.990
I uh...

20:47.000 --> 20:47.990
I just...

20:48.320 --> 20:50.231
I was out of weed,

20:50.320 --> 20:53.790
so I bought
a dime bag from Packy?

20:55.200 --> 20:56.679
You know with the uh...

21:07.200 --> 21:10.431
Not safe
around here for us.

21:11.560 --> 21:12.595
SIMONE: Yeah?

21:12.680 --> 21:14.239
Wow.

21:14.320 --> 21:15.594
No one tells me nothing.

21:18.040 --> 21:19.394
But I'll...

21:19.480 --> 21:22.199
Look, I can score
weed at other places.

21:22.280 --> 21:24.078
Thanks for the, uh...

21:24.160 --> 21:26.231
BEAR: Come on,
I'll give you a ride.

21:29.800 --> 21:31.313
Got my car.

21:32.160 --> 21:34.037
Ricky'll drive it back.

21:40.800 --> 21:42.359
You two have fun, huh?

22:04.760 --> 22:06.751
(RICKY STARTING ENGINE)

22:11.680 --> 22:13.717
Seatbelt on.

22:15.920 --> 22:17.035
So,

22:17.120 --> 22:20.875
is this a conversation about how it's
time for me to pack up and go home?

22:20.960 --> 22:21.950
LOU: No.

22:22.040 --> 22:23.394
Don't have to go home.

22:24.160 --> 22:25.673
It's a big country.

22:26.440 --> 22:27.794
Just maybe don't be here.

22:29.880 --> 22:32.190
Are you familiar with the
phrase "manifest destiny"?

22:32.840 --> 22:35.070
Yeah, but see,
here's the thing.

22:35.160 --> 22:37.356
I own two pairs of shoes.

22:37.440 --> 22:39.954
A summer pair
and one for winter.

22:41.800 --> 22:44.553
We're not meant to have
more than we can handle,

22:45.160 --> 22:46.639
is what I mean.

22:47.360 --> 22:49.271
So, this need for conquest,
you know,

22:50.440 --> 22:52.636
trying to own things that
aren't meant to be owned...

22:52.720 --> 22:53.949
Like people?

22:54.640 --> 22:56.119
That's an example.

22:57.360 --> 22:58.919
But also places.

23:00.520 --> 23:02.636
Believing we can tame things.

23:03.360 --> 23:05.317
That's a problem, right?

23:05.600 --> 23:07.193
Not a solution.

23:07.680 --> 23:09.637
MIKE: You're saying
capitalism is a problem?

23:10.880 --> 23:12.154
No.

23:12.720 --> 23:13.755
Greed.

23:15.320 --> 23:17.152
Making this
thing all or nothing.

23:17.880 --> 23:19.791
(DOOR OPENS)

23:24.240 --> 23:26.311
What happened to you?
What happened? Mmm?

23:28.000 --> 23:30.196
What happened? Let's
just get this over with.

23:34.960 --> 23:37.236
So, you got a response
to my "all-or-nothing" line?

23:39.960 --> 23:41.951
Sometimes...

23:42.040 --> 23:43.678
There's a man.

23:43.760 --> 23:45.592
BEN: What? What man?

23:45.680 --> 23:48.513
Just a man,
works in a factory.

23:49.520 --> 23:51.318
One day the boss
gets it in his mind

23:51.440 --> 23:53.238
that this man is
stealing from him.

23:53.320 --> 23:55.994
So, every night
at the gate,

23:56.120 --> 23:58.031
the guards search
his wheelbarrow.

23:59.040 --> 24:01.031
But they never
find anything.

24:01.120 --> 24:02.474
BEN: Pat him down.

24:02.560 --> 24:03.755
Oh, they do that.

24:03.840 --> 24:05.353
Strip him naked.

24:06.480 --> 24:07.709
Nothing.

24:09.800 --> 24:12.155
So, he's not stealing.

24:14.920 --> 24:16.240
Of course he is.

24:17.600 --> 24:18.829
Wheelbarrows.

24:20.640 --> 24:24.873
Thank you. That's right.
He's stealing wheelbarrows.

24:27.080 --> 24:28.798
What?

24:28.880 --> 24:30.518
My point is,

24:30.880 --> 24:33.110
sometimes the answer
IS SO obvious,

24:34.160 --> 24:37.198
you can't see it 'cause
you're looking too hard.

24:38.960 --> 24:42.555
See, we can't leave
because we're the future,

24:43.960 --> 24:45.394
and they're the past.

24:47.080 --> 24:48.957
The past can no more
become the future

24:49.040 --> 24:50.872
than the future
can become the past.

24:53.920 --> 24:55.240
Okay.

24:56.440 --> 24:57.953
We said our piece.

25:01.360 --> 25:02.714
Just don't be
offended next time

25:02.800 --> 25:05.918
if I don't say
"hello" before I shoot.

25:09.240 --> 25:10.230
(SIGHS)

25:14.880 --> 25:16.917
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

25:52.800 --> 25:54.791
(SIZZLING)

25:57.480 --> 25:58.993
Jeez. ..
Huh?

25:59.400 --> 26:01.437
(BETSY BREATHING HEAVILY)

26:01.600 --> 26:06.151
Karl Weathers! That is a
good way to get yourself shot.

26:06.480 --> 26:09.757
Your lesser half
gave us a key.

26:09.880 --> 26:12.872
Asked us to look out for you
and the little one while he's gone.

26:15.280 --> 26:17.556
Do I strike you as someone
who needs looking after?

26:17.680 --> 26:19.000
KARL: You do not.

26:19.320 --> 26:20.993
But he asked. So here we are.

26:21.080 --> 26:24.994
I'll sleep on the sofa. Sonny's
already called dibs on the floor.

26:25.520 --> 26:26.635
Wait, did what?

26:26.720 --> 26:29.599
I'd give you the sofa,
see, except for my back.

26:29.680 --> 26:30.670
What's the matter
with your back?

26:30.760 --> 26:32.797
It hurts when I
sleep on the floor.

26:33.680 --> 26:37.071
Eggs are done, pancakes
are warming in the oven.

26:37.160 --> 26:39.356
You can fight me on
are-we-gonna-stay-the-night,

26:39.440 --> 26:41.431
or you and the kid
could grab a plate,

26:41.520 --> 26:45.354
and see why they call me
the Breakfast King of Loyola.

27:19.000 --> 27:20.957
Any word from Grandma?

27:26.600 --> 27:29.513
I saw they took her.
The police.

27:31.400 --> 27:35.155
She's tough, though.
It's not like they'd...

27:37.440 --> 27:39.272
And like I said,
I was just...

27:40.920 --> 27:42.399
You know, |I...

27:42.480 --> 27:45.074
Dodd told everybody on
our side not to sell to me.

27:46.560 --> 27:48.836
Weed, you know. And so...

27:51.240 --> 27:54.756
I mean, sometimes a girl just
wants to bust a nut, you know?

28:10.600 --> 28:12.432
How come you don't
ask about Charlie?

28:12.520 --> 28:13.840
What?

28:16.600 --> 28:21.276
You ask about Floyd and
your dad, but not about Charlie.

28:22.080 --> 28:25.357
Well, I mean,
yeah, sure, how's he...

28:25.440 --> 28:28.353
State pen,
waiting for trial.

28:28.440 --> 28:31.000
Well, we should,
I mean, visit.

28:31.080 --> 28:33.276
Except, maybe Dodd...

28:33.360 --> 28:34.794
Dad.

28:35.440 --> 28:36.589
What?

28:37.040 --> 28:40.476
His name's not Dodd
to you. It's Dad.

28:41.560 --> 28:43.119
Bullshit.

28:43.960 --> 28:45.792
After everything he did?

28:47.160 --> 28:49.117
That you've seen him
do to me,

28:50.600 --> 28:53.399
which you don't even wanna
think about what he does...

28:53.480 --> 28:55.676
Not defending him.
...ilf you're not around.

28:55.760 --> 28:57.876
Just telling you
what he is to you.

29:00.200 --> 29:01.998
What's he to you?

29:18.720 --> 29:20.233
Where are we going?

29:46.400 --> 29:47.799
BEAR: Come.

29:48.880 --> 29:50.154
SIMONE: No.

29:56.040 --> 29:57.553
That's not...

30:00.080 --> 30:01.798
Come.

30:01.880 --> 30:03.871
You're scaring me.

30:06.760 --> 30:08.751
(STRUGGLING)

30:16.880 --> 30:17.915
Stop.

30:23.080 --> 30:24.639
He took my boy.

30:25.400 --> 30:26.390
What?

30:26.480 --> 30:28.278
Used his snake
tongue and took him.

30:30.080 --> 30:31.912
Walked him
right out the door.

30:33.920 --> 30:35.433
That's what your dad
is to me.

30:35.560 --> 30:37.597
Look, I didn't...

30:38.520 --> 30:40.431
It wasn't against you.

30:40.520 --> 30:41.954
What I did...

30:42.040 --> 30:43.951
I didn't mean for...

30:44.040 --> 30:47.749
Doesn't matter what you mean.
It's what you do.

30:50.360 --> 30:52.192
Sleeping with the enemy.

30:53.840 --> 30:57.720
In France,
after the Second War,

30:59.640 --> 31:02.280
they shaved a lady's head
for bedding the Germans,

31:03.760 --> 31:05.831
then they ran her outta town.

31:07.280 --> 31:08.600
Or worse.

31:11.040 --> 31:13.077
(SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING)

31:51.800 --> 31:52.870
I can help.

31:54.320 --> 31:55.674
They trust me.

31:57.000 --> 31:58.115
I could...

31:58.720 --> 32:00.950
I don't know,
I could give them information.

32:01.040 --> 32:04.112
Fake information,
and you could...

32:04.200 --> 32:05.190
Not our way.

32:05.360 --> 32:06.759
Yeah, but...

32:07.200 --> 32:08.190
I mean, they're...

32:09.200 --> 32:10.952
How many dead now?

32:12.000 --> 32:13.479
They're kicking our ass.

32:14.440 --> 32:15.794
That's on you.

32:17.960 --> 32:21.351
Your uncle,
your own grandfather.

32:24.880 --> 32:25.915
That's you.

32:28.360 --> 32:29.589
No.

32:31.240 --> 32:33.880
You, don't do that.

32:35.640 --> 32:37.199
Put this on me.

32:38.720 --> 32:42.156
Grandma wanted to negotiate,
but Dodd...

32:43.880 --> 32:46.190
Dad wouldn't let her.

32:47.960 --> 32:49.189
He did this.

32:50.400 --> 32:52.630
He made it war.
He's a snake, like you said.

32:52.720 --> 32:55.678
A rat.
He took Charlie, not me.

32:57.480 --> 33:01.713
I was just...
I'm the victim here.

33:03.000 --> 33:06.118
What was I supposed to do?

33:09.040 --> 33:10.553
Kneel down now.

33:27.840 --> 33:28.830
SIMONE: (TREMBLING) Please.

33:29.840 --> 33:31.239
Please.

33:31.800 --> 33:33.154
It's not...

33:35.120 --> 33:36.599
We're family.

33:39.520 --> 33:41.591
None of us are family anymore.

33:42.160 --> 33:44.037
(GUN COCKING)
(SIMONE WAILING)

33:44.120 --> 33:45.394
Please!

33:47.320 --> 33:48.594
Please!

33:50.040 --> 33:51.997
Please. Please, just...

33:53.120 --> 33:54.440
Banish me.

33:55.280 --> 33:57.112
Like you said, shave my head.

33:59.400 --> 34:03.837
Run me out of... I'll go,
I'll go away and never...

34:07.440 --> 34:08.953
You don't have to...

34:10.159 --> 34:11.672
BEAR: Hush now.

34:20.480 --> 34:22.437
It's already done.

34:22.600 --> 34:27.993
(SINGING) Oh, Danny Boy

34:29.120 --> 34:34.638
The pipes,
the pipes are calling

34:36.840 --> 34:42.755
From glen to glen

34:42.840 --> 34:48.835
And down the mountain side

34:51.120 --> 34:56.320
The summer's gone

34:56.440 --> 35:03.153
And all the roses falling

35:05.760 --> 35:11.756
It's you, it's you must go

35:12.520 --> 35:15.956
And I must bide

35:21.880 --> 35:26.431
But come ye back

35:26.560 --> 35:33.159
When summer's in the meadow

35:35.760 --> 35:41.472
Or when the valley's

35:41.560 --> 35:48.079
Hushed and white with snow

35:50.360 --> 35:55.753
And I'll be here

35:56.240 --> 35:59.756
In sunshine

35:59.840 --> 36:03.959
Or in shadow

36:06.160 --> 36:13.078
Oh, Danny boy

36:13.640 --> 36:16.758
I love you so

36:16.840 --> 36:18.513
Guy called
for you again.

36:18.600 --> 36:19.999
What guy?

36:20.080 --> 36:22.754
Says he knows Dodd,
where he is.

36:25.920 --> 36:27.354
What did you say?

36:27.480 --> 36:28.879
I told him you were out.

36:29.560 --> 36:30.550
Argh!

36:30.640 --> 36:33.029
Did the men hear?
They know?

36:33.600 --> 36:34.635
No.

36:34.720 --> 36:37.553
Shit, man. I don't say
nothing unless you tell me.

36:40.000 --> 36:42.958
There's no Dodd,
you hear? Not anymore.

36:44.120 --> 36:45.519
He calls back,
this guy, you tell him

36:45.640 --> 36:48.154
to sell that
shit some place else.

36:48.240 --> 36:50.390
We got all the crazy
we can handle.

36:51.840 --> 36:52.830
(GRUNTS)

36:57.200 --> 36:58.952
Kind of cold,
don't you think?

37:14.000 --> 37:15.320
What?

37:17.560 --> 37:18.914
Nothing.

37:20.240 --> 37:21.833
Family business.

37:23.360 --> 37:24.839
Not my place.

37:33.120 --> 37:37.512
People think it's morbid,
but I think it's beautiful.

37:39.960 --> 37:41.917
(PHONE RINGING)

37:42.000 --> 37:43.911
I got it.

37:47.320 --> 37:48.594
Solversons.

37:48.680 --> 37:49.909
LOU: Yeah, it's me.

37:50.840 --> 37:52.513
Still breathing?

37:52.840 --> 37:53.910
Thank God.

37:54.040 --> 37:55.758
The boys there?

37:55.840 --> 37:58.673
Do you mean
the King of Breakfast?

37:59.240 --> 38:00.230
LOU: Huh?

38:00.520 --> 38:01.510
(CHUCKLES)

38:02.400 --> 38:04.869
I don't need
looking after, you know.

38:05.920 --> 38:07.558
How long
we've been together?

38:08.720 --> 38:10.358
Well it's all hands
on deck, hon.

38:10.840 --> 38:12.956
You don't know how
bad it is out there.

38:13.040 --> 38:14.758
Nope, tell me.

38:14.840 --> 38:16.478
Well, I'm telling you.

38:17.280 --> 38:18.395
Is Karl drinking?

38:18.720 --> 38:20.472
MOLLY: Karl, can you read
me another story?

38:20.560 --> 38:22.631
Not unless beer counts.

38:22.960 --> 38:24.678
How's Molly?

38:24.760 --> 38:25.955
Short.

38:26.080 --> 38:28.071
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

38:28.720 --> 38:31.792
And Noreen? She still there?

38:31.880 --> 38:33.234
Yeah, she's good.

38:33.720 --> 38:35.358
Molly likes her,

38:35.800 --> 38:38.918
and she's helping.

38:40.080 --> 38:42.469
And you? You feel okay?

38:42.560 --> 38:45.837
Better than some.
Worse than others.

38:45.920 --> 38:47.319
Well, can you rest?

38:48.120 --> 38:51.750
How am I supposed to rest? You
keep telling me how bad things are.

38:54.920 --> 38:57.753
Ask Karl about
John McCain's thumbscrews.

38:57.840 --> 38:59.592
What?

38:59.680 --> 39:01.478
He said to tell you

39:01.560 --> 39:03.358
that if John
McCain could survive

39:03.480 --> 39:05.198
five years in Viet
Cong thumbscrews,

39:05.320 --> 39:07.231
you could beat cancer.

39:07.640 --> 39:08.630
(BETSY CHUCKLING)

39:08.760 --> 39:11.957
Well, yeah, I don't know
about that... My daughter?

39:12.040 --> 39:14.759
But I'm trying.

39:16.440 --> 39:17.589
Your dad says hi.

39:17.920 --> 39:19.069
Say hi back.

39:19.160 --> 39:21.549
HANK: Yeah, tell her
don't forget to feed my cats.

39:21.640 --> 39:24.837
LOU: He said to tell you...
Yeah, yeah, I heard.

39:27.680 --> 39:28.954
Come home soon.

39:29.120 --> 39:30.394
Okay?

39:31.800 --> 39:32.790
I will.

39:49.240 --> 39:50.799
Everything okay?

39:52.160 --> 39:53.559
Oh, yeah.

39:57.080 --> 40:00.630
Well, looks like
Floyd's gonna flip.

40:00.720 --> 40:02.472
Yeah?
Yeah, took some doing,

40:02.560 --> 40:03.709
but we convinced her

40:03.800 --> 40:07.111
the only way this thing was
gonna end up in the win column,

40:07.200 --> 40:09.840
was if she puts
us in the game.

40:11.280 --> 40:12.270
Hmm.

40:14.480 --> 40:17.313
Okay, first, I want...

40:18.080 --> 40:21.391
I want it on the record that
this is a road of last resort.

40:22.720 --> 40:24.119
My husband...

40:25.880 --> 40:27.075
Second,

40:27.160 --> 40:29.800
I need assurances that
none of my children,

40:29.880 --> 40:32.440
or my grandchildren are in
line for any repercussions.

40:32.520 --> 40:33.510
This is my choice.

40:33.880 --> 40:37.191
My war. They're just
doing what they're told.

40:38.000 --> 40:39.957
Capital crimes excluded.

40:41.200 --> 40:42.554
FLOYD: What's that
supposed to mean?

40:43.400 --> 40:45.311
Murder in the first
and the like.

40:46.200 --> 40:48.794
What's the point of the damn
deal if it doesn't cover murder?

40:48.880 --> 40:51.076
From this point forth,
he's saying.

40:52.200 --> 40:53.474
New crimes.

40:54.280 --> 40:57.318
Now, time you tell
us what you know.

41:03.880 --> 41:06.190
Don't you look at
me with those eyes.

41:07.040 --> 41:08.713
None of you are mothers.

41:16.400 --> 41:17.390
Kansas City

41:18.360 --> 41:22.240
runs most of their dope through
an outfit called Legit Truckin'

41:22.320 --> 41:24.072
out of Cincinnati.

41:26.360 --> 41:28.636
My information is they hide it
in the tires.

41:31.520 --> 41:35.400
Here in town, they store their
gak in two different places.

41:35.480 --> 41:38.313
There's a nail
salon on Robertson.

41:38.400 --> 41:41.472
And an auto
repair shop on First.

41:41.600 --> 41:44.240
And check the air pump inside.

41:47.080 --> 41:50.072
Also, I hear they got weapons

41:51.120 --> 41:53.396
stashed on the roof.

41:54.280 --> 41:56.271
(PHONE RINGING)

42:27.000 --> 42:29.037
(PHONE RINGING)

42:37.800 --> 42:39.837
(PHONE TAKEN OFF HOOK)

42:58.000 --> 42:59.559
Hello.

42:59.680 --> 43:01.557
MAN: The Undertaker's coming.

43:01.680 --> 43:03.114
You're done.

43:33.200 --> 43:34.395
Okay?
Yeah.

43:35.000 --> 43:37.071
Get word to Hanzee.
Tell him to come in.

43:37.160 --> 43:38.798
And find Dodd.

43:38.880 --> 43:39.836
How?

43:39.920 --> 43:41.991
Don't care how.
War's almost won.

43:42.120 --> 43:44.191
Gotta finish them
while they're reeling.

43:53.040 --> 43:54.519
What do you think?

43:56.040 --> 43:58.031
I think we just
chose a side.

44:04.160 --> 44:06.834
Indian shot two
troopers in South Dakota.

44:06.920 --> 44:08.319
What? What Indian?

44:08.400 --> 44:09.356
Ours.

44:09.440 --> 44:12.717
Description matches the
Gerhardt's man, been missing.

44:13.480 --> 44:15.517
Where?
Sioux Falls.

44:16.240 --> 44:19.119
Witness said the
Indian shot up a bar

44:19.200 --> 44:21.271
and that he was looking
for a young couple.

44:21.640 --> 44:22.789
Man of which
being a redhead.

44:22.920 --> 44:24.069
Peggy and Ed.

44:24.160 --> 44:26.879
It's South Dakota's problem,
it sounds like.

44:26.960 --> 44:28.473
HANK: That's one way
to think about it.

44:28.600 --> 44:30.637
So, the Indian,
probably he got away, yeah?

44:30.920 --> 44:31.990
Oh, yeah. Yeah.

44:32.080 --> 44:35.391
One trooper dead,
one clinging to life.

44:36.520 --> 44:39.876
Still, pursuit means
they could be close.

44:39.960 --> 44:42.236
Right? Peggy and Ed?
Holed up somewhere.

44:42.320 --> 44:43.355
Or on the road.

44:43.440 --> 44:46.193
If we're lucky, yeah. The
troopers got road blocks set up.

44:46.760 --> 44:48.194
Then there's Dodd.

44:48.280 --> 44:50.476
Usually where the
Indian goes, Dodd's there.

44:50.560 --> 44:51.880
Witness just saw the Indian.

44:52.000 --> 44:54.276
Except remember,

44:54.360 --> 44:56.954
we just promised to give
the Gerhardts a free pass.

44:58.800 --> 45:01.599
You better run it by the
captain. That's all I'm saying.

45:04.360 --> 45:07.000
You're a shit cop.
You know that, right?

45:11.040 --> 45:15.511
Getting promoted next month,
so how bad could it be?

45:16.880 --> 45:18.393
Stay then.

45:18.480 --> 45:20.676
Maybe we'll go see if
we can save the day.

45:38.840 --> 45:40.638
Stop it.

45:41.920 --> 45:44.799
I'm fine.
I feel fine.

45:47.440 --> 45:48.669
Good.

45:53.520 --> 45:58.276
He worries too much.
Like this, sending you over.

45:58.680 --> 45:59.715
Mmm.

45:59.800 --> 46:00.870
Men.

46:01.840 --> 46:03.513
(BETSY CHUCKLING)

46:04.160 --> 46:05.480
Shut up.

46:08.000 --> 46:10.037
He was supposed to
marry my sister, you know.

46:10.520 --> 46:12.477
Lenore, the older.

46:12.560 --> 46:13.675
BETSY: After high school.

46:14.400 --> 46:18.314
She used to say, "I'm gonna
marry that boy someday."

46:19.920 --> 46:22.719
But then there was Vietnam
and he joined up,

46:23.720 --> 46:26.758
and she never was very
good at waiting. So he got me.

46:30.240 --> 46:31.799
The dud.

46:31.880 --> 46:34.349
Listen, if I was building
an ark and they said,

46:34.440 --> 46:37.432
"You can only take two people,
man and wife,"

46:37.840 --> 46:40.958
I'd take him and you
over him and her any day.

46:44.480 --> 46:46.153
You'll look after them.

46:49.080 --> 46:50.479
Right?

46:55.840 --> 46:59.196
My dad'll help, but he'll need
looking after too, before too long.

47:01.720 --> 47:03.438
You got the new pills.

47:03.920 --> 47:05.194
Xanadu.

47:06.280 --> 47:07.509
No.

47:08.960 --> 47:10.473
They gave me the sugar ones.

47:12.640 --> 47:13.994
I'm pretty sure.

47:18.600 --> 47:21.991
Tell him if he needs to
get married again, it's okay.

47:23.600 --> 47:25.955
Just not Rhonda Knutson.

47:29.800 --> 47:32.713
Her eyes are too small or too
close together or something.

47:34.280 --> 47:35.634
It's weird.

47:39.240 --> 47:40.514
Listen,
if John McCain could...

47:40.640 --> 47:41.960
BETSY: Karl Weathers.

47:44.040 --> 47:45.997
Don't you be silly now.

47:47.600 --> 47:50.274
John McCain was
a fighter pilot.

